  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "English/ Chinese Preschool Educator",
  "description": "<h2>L1 / L2 Chinese Language & English Language Teacher</h2><h3>Join a Nurturing, Fun & Supportive Preschool Environment</h3><p>We are looking for <strong>passionate and qualified L1 / L2 Chinese Language and English Language Teachers</strong> who believe in nurturing the whole child and growing together as a team.</p><h3>Role Summary</h3><p>You will be responsible for creating a <strong>safe, engaging, and developmentally appropriate learning environment</strong> where children feel loved, respected, and excited to learn. Working closely with a <strong>nurturing and supportive Principal</strong>, you will deliver quality lessons while building strong relationships with children, parents, and colleagues.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Plan and deliver engaging <strong>Chinese Language or English Language lessons</strong> aligned with the preschool curriculum</p></li><li><p>Foster children’s <strong>holistic development</strong> through purposeful play and structured learning</p></li><li><p>Maintain a <strong>small staff-child ratio</strong>, allowing meaningful interaction and individualised attention</p></li><li><p>Observe, document, and support children’s learning progress</p></li><li><p>Communicate effectively with parents and collaborate with the teaching team</p></li><li><p>Uphold centre policies, ECDA standards, and professional teaching practices</p></li></ul><h3>Working Hours & Environment</h3><ul><li><p><strong>8-hour workday</strong> with a <strong>1-hour lunch break</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Delicious meals provided daily</strong></p></li><li><p>Fun, positive, and <strong>loving work environment</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong emphasis on <strong>work-life balance</strong></p></li><li><p>Supportive and nurturing school leadership that values staff well-being</p></li></ul><h3>Staff Benefits & Welfare</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Mental Wellness Day Off</strong> (because your well-being matters)</p></li><li><p><strong>Birthday Off</strong> to celebrate you</p></li><li><p><strong>Work Anniversary Vouchers</strong> as our way of saying thank you</p></li><li><p>Staff appreciation initiatives and a caring work culture</p></li><li><p>Stable management and a respectful, family-oriented team</p></li></ul><p>If you are passionate about early childhood education and are looking for a workplace that truly values its teachers, we would love to hear from you.</p><p>📩 <em>Apply now and grow with us in a centre where teachers are respected, supported, and appreciated.</em></p>",
